  <text id="volume_08">
    <body>
      <div1 id="BQ-08-4-0002">
      	<pb id="p08-107" n="107"/>
          <head>
            <title type="main">
              <hi rend="b">Works in Progress</hi>
            </title>
          </head>
          <p>B. H. Fairchild, Jr.: “‘Such Holy Song’: Music as Idea, Form, and Image in the Poetry of
William Blake,” a Ph.D. dissertation directed by Winston Weathers at the University of Tulsa, concentrating on
the <hi rend="i">melos</hi> of the <hi rend="i">Songs</hi>, the use of musical form and imagery in 
<hi rend="i">The Four Zoas</hi>, and the treatment of music as idea in Blake’s aesthetic and myth.</p>
          <p>Raymond Lister, Wolfson College, University of Cambridge: awarded a Senior Research Fellowship,
chiefly to assembly a full-scale critical catalogue of all the works of Samuel Palmer. Mr. Lister writes that
he would like to hear from anybody who knows of the location of any such works, particularly those in private
collections. Address c/o Windmill House, Linton, Cambridge, England CB1 6NS.</p>
      </div1>
